Fresearch%252Fretirement-crisis-401k%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJuly%202024%20report%20on%20the%20state%20of%20retirement%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%2C%20among%20other%20results%2C%20examined%20the%20likelihood%20that%20different%20generations%20will%20have%20sufficient%20savings%20as%20they%20enter%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20found%20that%C2%A0millennials%20and%20Gen%20Zers%20are%20at%20lower%20risk%20of%20having%20a%20savings%20shortfall%20in%20retirement%20than%20Gen%20X%20and%20boomers%2C%20due%20in%20large%20part%20to%20major%20changes%20over%20the%20last%20several%20decades%20in%20how%20retirement%20benefits%20are%20structured.%20Assuming%20no%20changes%20to%20Social%20Security%20benefits%2C%2037%25%20of%20Gen%20Z%20and%2044%25%20of%20millennials%20could%20experience%20retirement%20shortfalls%2C%20coming%20in%20below%2047%25%20of%20Gen%20X%20and%2052%25%20of%20boomers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FrjUmt%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Potential%20retirement%20shortfalls%20by%20generation%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22501%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20findings%20are%20based%20on%20Morningstar's%20model%20of%20US%20retirement%20outcomes%2C%20which%20simulates%20whether%20Americans%20will%20have%20sufficient%20income%20in%20retirement%20based%20on%20a%20representative%20sample%20of%20US%20households%20using%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalreserve.gov%2Feconres%2Fscfindex.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2022%20Survey%20of%20Consumer%20Finances%3C%2Fa%3E%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOlder%20Americans%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-retirement-of-peak-boomers-could-affect-economy-social-security-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincreasingly%20struggling%20to%20stay%20financially%20afloat%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20they%20enter%20retirement.%20The%20issue%20is%20especially%20prevalent%20for%20the%20younger%20cohorts%20of%20the%20baby%20boomers%20%E2%80%94%20over%2030%20million%20of%20them%20born%20between%201959%20and%201964%20are%20starting%20to%20turn%2065%20this%20year%2C%20and%20a%20recent%20report%20from%20the%20Alliance%20for%20Lifetime%20Income's%20Retirement%20Income%20Institute%20found%20that%2052.5%25%20of%20them%20have%20%24250%2C000%20or%20less%20in%20assets.%20Additionally%2C%20many%20of%20them%20did%20not%20have%20the%20same%20types%20of%20retirement%20accounts%20that%20now%20exist%20for%20younger%20generations%2C%20meaning%20they'll%20have%20to%20drain%20their%20savings%20and%20rely%20on%20Social%20Security%20to%20get%20by%20in%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%2068-year-old%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomer-retirement-social-security-insurance-cancer-diagnosis-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20BI%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20she%20cannot%20afford%20to%20retire%20and%20is%20living%20off%20her%20Social%20Security%20and%20salary.%20%26quot%3BI%20used%20to%20say%20this%20all%20the%20time%20as%20a%20joke%2C%20I'm%20going%20to%20have%20to%20work%20until%20the%20day%20I%20die%20because%20I%20can't%20possibly%20ever%20afford%20to%20retire%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b68c8cf6-f05a-46ad-bf7e-eefc2753798c%5C%22%3EThe%20changing%20retirement%20savings%20landscape%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESpencer%20Look%2C%20associate%20director%20of%20retirement%20studies%20at%20Morningstar%20Retirement%20and%20one%20of%20the%20report's%20authors%2C%20said%20Morningstar%20defined%20retirement%20shortfalls%20as%20%26quot%3Bcases%20where%20the%20household%20was%20not%20able%20to%20fund%20typical%20expenses%20and%20long%20term%20supports%20and%20services%20costs%20throughout%20retirement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELook%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20millennials%20and%20Gen%20Z%20benefit%20from%20a%20range%20of%20products%20that%20didn't%20exist%20for%20older%20generations%20previously%2C%20including%20auto-enrollment%20in%20savings%20accounts%20and%20diffenrent%20types%20of%20retirement%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BBaby%20boomers%20and%20Gen%20Xers%20may%20have%20lower%20levels%20of%20retirement%20savings%20because%20they%20were%20impacted%20by%20the%20transition%20from%26quot%3B%20a%20defined-benefit-dominant%20system%2C%20which%20includes%20pensions%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eto%20one%20that's%20dominated%20by%20defined%20contribution%20accounts%2C%20such%20as%20401(k)%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-savings-401k-pension-real-estate-investments-baby-boomers-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPensions%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20or%20payouts%20employers%20offer%20to%20former%20employees%20%E2%80%94%20have%20dwindled%20in%20the%20US%20over%20recent%20years.%20The%20more%20popular%20form%20of%20savings%20is%20401(k)s%2C%20in%20which%20workers%20and%20their%20employers%20contribute%20to%20the%20funds%20while%20employed%20to%20bolster%20their%20savings%20once%20they%20retire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20those%20who%20spent%20large%20parts%20of%20their%20careers%20between%20those%20two%20systems%20may%20not%20gain%20the%20benefits%20of%20either.%20%26quot%3BHaving%20that%20uncertainty%20and%20that%20transition%2C%20it%20definitely%20shows%20up%20because%20the%20results%20in%20our%20model%20are%20much%20more%20driven%20by%20current%20levels%20of%20savings%20because%20these%20folks%20have%20less%20time%20left%20in%20their%20working%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Look%20said%20about%20boomers%20and%20Gen%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20folks%20just%20really%20don't%20think%20their%20finances%20will%20be%20enough%20to%20sustain%20the%20lifestyle%20they%20want%20in%20retirement%2C%20I%20know%20it's%20not%20something%20people%20want%20to%20hear%2C%20but%20working%20a%20little%20bit%20longer%20or%20working%20part%20time%2C%20that%20can%20go%20a%20long%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Look%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELook%20added%20that%20while%20he%20knows%20delaying%20retirement%20isn't%20a%20possible%20situation%20for%20all%2C%20he%20pointed%20out%20it%20could%20help%20prevent%20those%20shortfalls.%20According%20to%20the%20report%2C%20only%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Earound%2028%25%20of%20US%20households%20would%20face%20retirement%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eshortfalls%20if%20they%20retire%20at%2070.%20Meanwhile%2C%20this%20figure%20was%2054%25%20for%20age%2062%2C%2045%25%20at%20Morningstar's%20baseline%20retirement%20age%20of%2065%2C%20and%2038%25%20for%20retiring%20at%2067.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20%26quot%3Bcan%20make%20a%20really%20big%20difference%2C%26quot%3B%20Look%20said%20about%20delaying%20retirement%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20not%20only%20have%20more%20time%20accumulating%20your%20assets%20and%20hopefully%20growing%20with%20the%20capital%20markets%2C%26quot%3B%20Look%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20delay%20claiming%20Social%20Security%20and%20get%20a%20bigger%20benefit%20and%20inflation-adjusted%20benefit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHow%20are%20you%20making%20or%20planning%20to%20make%20ends%20meet%20in%20retirement%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20these%20reporters%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aasheffey%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Easheffey%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Amhoff%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Emhoff%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-security-retirement-shortfalls-boomers-gen-x-millennial-gen-z-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%