%20the%20billionaires%20on%20the%202023%20Forbes%20400%20list%20%E2%80%94%20the%20400%20richest%20people%20in%20the%20United%20States%20%E2%80%94%2070%25%20are%20basically%20self-made.%20And%2059%25%20came%20from%20an%20upper-middle-class%20background%20or%20below.%20This%20phenomenon%20is%20even%20more%20true%20the%20farther%20you%20go%20along%20the%20tail%20of%20the%20wealth%20curve.%20All%20of%20the%2010%20richest%20people%20in%20America%20are%20classified%20as%20self-made.%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fjonathanponciano%2F2020%2F09%2F08%2Fself-made-score%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EForbes%3C%2Fa%3E%20treats%20the%20question%20as%20a%20sliding%20scale%20from%201%20to%2010%3B%20those%20with%20scores%20of%206%20or%20higher%20were%20considered%20self-made).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20number%20is%20significantly%20higher%20than%20it%20once%20was.%20In%201982%2C%20only%2040%25%20of%20the%20Forbes%20400%20had%20started%20their%20own%20business%3B%20the%20majority%20were%20simply%20scions%20of%20inherited%20wealth.%20Old%20money%20is%20out%2C%20new%20money%20is%20in%3F%20Well%2C%20it's%20essential%20to%20keep%20in%20mind%20that%20this%20is%20not%20an%20indication%20of%20overall%20social%20mobility%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20In%20fact%2C%20by%20most%20accounts%2C%20such%20as%20the%20extremely%20detailed%20work%20of%20the%20economist%20Raj%20Chetty%2C%20overall%20income%20and%20wealth%20mobility%20has%20decreased%20in%20the%20US%20from%20a%20generation%20ago.%20The%20Forbes%20400%2C%20however%2C%20is%20the%20extreme%20right%20tail%20of%20the%20curve.%20To%20wind%20up%20there%2C%20it%20helps%20to%20have%20made%20some%20extremely%20risky%20bets%20that%20paid%20off%20%E2%80%94%20ones%20that%20you%20have%20less%20incentive%20to%20take%20if%20you're%20already%20rich.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELet's%20say%20you%20inherit%20a%20%2425%20million%20trust%20fund%20on%20your%2018th%20birthday.%20Are%20you%20going%20to%20start%20a%20business%20with%20it%3F%20Maybe%20you%20should.%20But%20it's%20much%20easier%20to%20withdraw%20%241%20million%20a%20year%20to%20live%20off%2C%20travel%20the%20world%20and%20have%20some%20wild%20parties%2C%20and%20put%20the%20rest%20in%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20index%20funds%20earning%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E7%25%20a%20year.%20By%20the%20time%20you're%2065%2C%20your%20expected%20net%20worth%20is%20about%20%24250%20million%20%E2%80%94%20plus%20a%20whole%20lot%20of%20frequent%20flyer%20miles.%20Nice!%20You're%20very%2C%20very%20rich.%20But%20you're%20not%20sniffing%20the%20Forbes%20400%20list%2C%20where%20the%20bidding%20starts%20at%20about%20%243%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConversely%2C%20there%20are%20about%205%20million%20new%20businesses%20founded%20in%20the%20US%20every%20year.%20That's%20a%20slightly%20misleading%20statistic%20because%20it%20includes%20things%20like%20a%20self-employed%20writer%2Fstatistician%2Fpoker%20player%20setting%20up%20a%20personal%20S%20corp%20for%20tax%20purposes.%20Still%2C%20if%20even%201%25%20of%20those%20startups%20have%20serious%20potential%20to%20scale%20up%2C%20that's%2050%2C000%20lottery%20tickets%20every%20year.%20Some%20of%20them%20are%20going%20to%20hit%20big%2C%20and%20the%20payoff%20for%20hitting%20big%20is%20so%20large%20these%20days%20that%20the%20lucky%20few%20who%20do%20are%20going%20to%20leapfrog%20all%20the%20trust%20fund%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20this%20certainly%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20you%20want%20to%20grow%20up%20in%20abject%20poverty%20if%20your%20goal%20is%20to%20launch%20a%20successful%20startup%20and%20get%20really%20rich%3B%20only%20a%20handful%20of%20the%20billionaires%20on%20the%20Forbes%20400%20list%20did.%20It%20helps%20to%20have%20a%20comfortable%20living%20environment.%20It%20also%20helps%20to%20be%20from%20one%20of%20the%20demographic%20classes%20that%20VCs%20like%20to%20invest%20in%20(e.g.%2C%20a%20nerdy%20young%20man%20of%20European%20or%20Asian%20ancestry).%20But%20people%20who%20are%20born%20on%20third%20base%20tend%20to%20be%20pretty%20risk-averse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhy%20are%20second-generation%20kids%20never%20that%20successful%3F%26quot%3B%20asked%20Social%20Capital%20CEO%20Chamath%20Palihapitiya%2C%20who%20moved%20with%20his%20family%20from%20Sri%20Lanka%20to%20Canada%20and%20worked%20at%20a%20Burger%20King%20to%20help%20support%20them.%20Instead%20of%20the%20entrepreneurial%20mother%20or%20father%2C%20who%20had%20%26quot%3Bonly%20one%20curve%20that%20they%20were%20optimizing%20for%2C%20which%20is%20the%20what-have-I-got-to-lose%20curve%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20child%20starts%20%26quot%3Bwith%20the%20exact%20inverse%20curve%20working%20against%20them%2C%20which%20is%20the%20risk%20of%20embarrassment%2C%26quot%3B%20Palihapitiya%20said.%20%26quot%3BNo%20matter%20what%20the%20parent%20says%20to%20that%20child%2C%20that%20person%20is%20operating%20from%20a%20perspective%20where%20the%20perception%20is%20that%20they%20have%20an%20enormous%20amount%20to%20lose.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20also%20help%20to%20have%20something%20else%3A%20a%20chip%20on%20your%20shoulder.%20Josh%20Wolfe%2C%20of%20Lux%20Capital%2C%20is%20fond%20of%20the%20phrase%20%26quot%3Bchips%20on%20shoulders%20put%20chips%20in%20pockets.%26quot%3B%20Feeling%20left%20out%2C%20excluded%2C%20or%20estranged%20can%20make%20you%20extremely%20competitive.%20VCs%20want%20founders%20who%20are%20willing%20to%20commit%20to%20low-probability%20ideas%20%E2%80%94%20ideas%20they%20think%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20is%20wrong%20about%20%E2%80%94%20for%20a%20decade%20or%20more.%20What%20motivates%20a%20person%20to%20do%20something%20like%20that%3F%20Wolfe%2C%20who%20grew%20up%20in%20a%20single-parent%20home%20in%20New%20York's%20gritty%20Coney%20Island%20neighborhood%2C%20told%20me%20he%20thinks%20there's%20a%20common%20answer%3A%20revenge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20could%20be%20because%20they%20were%20left%20for%20adoption.%20It%20could%20be%20a%20broken%20home%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20could%20be%20being%20the%20only%20minority%20in%20a%20mostly%20homogenous%20white%20neighborhood%2C%20or%20the%20obese%20kid%20in%20a%20Friday%20Night%20Lights%20football%20town.%20People%20that%20out%20of%20necessity%20grow%20a%20thick%20skin%20with%20not%20fitting%20in%20and%20being%20OK%20standing%20out.%20And%20feeling%20a%20sense%20of%20anger%20that%20is%20not%20leading%20them%20to%20despondence%2C%20but%20to%20motivated%20revenge.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ELet%20me%20make%20two%20things%20clear.%20First%2C%20you%20only%20want%20adversity%20up%20to%20a%20point.%20There%20is%20almost%20certainly%20a%20threshold%20beyond%20which%20there%20are%20too%20many%20disadvantages%20to%20overcome.%20Elon%20Musk%20had%20a%20difficult%20childhood%20and%20became%20estranged%20from%20his%20father%3B%20Thiel%20was%20gay%20and%20closeted%3B%20Jeff%20Bezos%20was%20adopted%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they%20were%20also%20privileged%20in%20other%20respects.%20They%20had%20chips%20on%20their%20shoulders%2C%20but%20they%20had%20enough%20social%20capital%20to%20be%20taken%20seriously%20by%20VCs%2C%20employees%2C%20and%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20second%2C%20this%20does%20not%20always%20turn%20out%20well.%20That%20competitive%20fire%20can%20be%20channeled%20in%20both%20constructive%20and%20self-destructive%20ways%2C%20and%20childhood%20trauma%20almost%20certainly%20has%20negative%20effects%20on%20the%20life%20course%20on%20average.%20But%20we're%20not%20talking%20about%20the%20average%3A%20We're%20talking%20about%20who%20winds%20up%20on%20the%20extreme%20right%20tail%2C%20the%200.0001%25.%20It's%20usually%20going%20to%20be%20people%20who%20are%20either%20irrationally%20risk-loving%20out%20of%20a%20sense%20of%20having%20nothing%20to%20lose%2C%20extraordinarily%20mission%20driven%20out%20of%20a%20sense%20of%20wanting%20to%20prove%20people%20wrong%20%E2%80%94%20or%20both%2C%20as%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Musk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20this%20is%20naturally%20going%20to%20lead%20to%20some%20difficult%20personalities.%20Some%20VCs%20even%20seem%20to%20think%20of%20it%20as%20an%20asset%20when%20a%20founder%20is%20poorly%20adjusted.%20%26quot%3BWho%20is%20my%20real%20customer%3F%20It's%20a%20young%2C%20disenfranchised%2C%20disenchanted%20entrepreneur-to-be%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Palihapitiya%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20sorts%20of%20people%20who%20might%20come%20to%20him%20for%20investment%20or%20mentorship.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20use%20those%20words%20specifically%2C%20because%20if%20you're%20comfortable%2C%20and%20you're%20happy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued%2C%20%26quot%3Byou're%20not%20the%20kind%20of%20person%20I%20want%20to%20work%20with%20anyway%20because%20you're%20probably%20not%20gonna%20be%20successful.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20feels%20like%20a%20dangerous%20game.%20Successful%20founders%20may%20be%20disagreeable%20on%20average%2C%20because%20disagreeability%20is%20correlated%20with%20competitiveness%20and%20independent-mindedness.%20But%20the%20disagreeability%20is%20still%20a%20bug%2C%20not%20a%20feature.%20If%20you%20start%20to%20select%20founders%20because%20they're%20disagreeable%2C%20you%20may%20get%20the%20wrong%20ones%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20if%20founders%20deliberately%20play%20into%20stereotypes%20that%20they%20think%20VCs%20will%20like%2C%20as%20Sam%20Bankman-Fried%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20if%20all%20you%20care%20about%20is%20the%20right%20tail%2C%20the%20selection%20process%20gets%20weird.%20Let's%20say%20you're%20starting%20a%20small%20business%20like%20an%20ice-cream%20shop.%20You%20just%20want%20to%20sell%20ice%20cream%20at%20one%20or%20two%20stores%20and%20make%20a%20decent%20living%20%E2%80%94%20not%20disrupt%20the%20global%20ice-cream%20business.%20You%20have%20the%20money%2C%20and%20you're%20looking%20for%20someone%20to%20run%20the%20operation.%20What%20characteristics%20should%20this%20person%20have%3F%20Words%20like%20reliable%2C%20trustworthy%2C%20hardworking%2C%20and%20agreeable%20come%20to%20mind.%20They'll%20give%20you%20the%20highest%20probability%20of%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20if%20you%20want%20a%20business%20that%20could%20grow%20by%20100x%20or%201%2C000x%3F%20That's%20a%20lot%20harder%20to%20know.%20I%20don't%20think%20VCs%20are%20deliberately%20picking%20founders%20they%20think%20are%20unreliable%2C%20although%20sometimes%20it%20seems%20like%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20August%202022%2C%20Andreessen%20Horowitz%20(A16z)%20announced%20its%20newest%20investment%3A%20It%20would%20put%20%24350%20million%20into%20a%20company%20called%20Flow%2C%20which%20%26quot%3Baims%20to%20create%20a%20superior%20living%20environment%20that%20enhances%20the%20lives%20of%20our%20residents%20and%20communities%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20in%20other%20words%2C%20rental%20real%20estate.%20The%20company%20was%20founded%20by%20a%20charismatic%20Israeli-American%20named%20Adam%20Neumann.%20If%20the%20name%20sounds%20familiar%2C%20it's%20because%20Neumann%20was%20also%20the%20founder%20of%20WeWork%20%E2%80%94%20a%20company%20that%20was%20once%20worth%20an%20estimated%20%2447%20billion%20before%20imploding%20spectacularly%20amid%20accusations%20that%20Neumann%20had%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20taken%20a%20%26quot%3Bsizable%20chunk%26quot%3B%20of%20weed%20across%20international%20borders%20on%20a%20private%20jet%2C%20fired%20a%20pregnant%20employee%2C%20and%20%E2%80%94%20most%20importantly%20%E2%80%94%20expanded%20far%20too%20quickly%2C%20leading%20to%20enormous%20annual%20losses.%20(Neumann%2C%20after%20directing%20me%20to%20a%20spokesperson%2C%20didn't%20respond%20to%20an%20interview%20request.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Book%20cover%20of%20%26quot%3BOn%20the%20Edge%26quot%3B%20by%20Nate%20Silver%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b4ebc5b4912df3ae19f9f7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222850%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EPenguin%20Press%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWould%20you%20want%20to%20go%20into%20business%20with%20someone%20like%20that%3F%20Well%2C%20I%20probably%20wouldn't%2C%20though%20the%20plane%20rides%20sound%20like%20fun.%20But%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%20terms%2C%20the%20thinking%20may%20go%20something%20like%20this%3A%20You'd%20rather%20invest%20in%20someone%20who%20had%20built%20a%20%2447%20billion%20company%20and%20watched%20it%20catastrophically%20collapse%20than%20someone%20who%20had%20never%20done%20so%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Andreessen%20Horowitz%20is%20proud%20of%20its%20investment%20in%20Flow.%20In%20February%202023%2C%20Marc%20Andreessen%20invited%20me%20to%20an%20A16z%20conference%20at%20the%20spectacularly%20beautiful%20Amangiri%20hotel%20in%20Canyon%20Point%2C%20Utah.%20I%20thought%20it%20would%20be%20worth%20going%20for%20the%20networking%20and%20the%20snowy%20desert%20landscapes%20even%20though%20I%20expected%20to%20be%20told%20that%20the%20event%20was%20off%20the%20record.%20Sure%20enough%2C%20at%20the%20first%20panel%2C%20Ben%20Horowitz%20said%20the%20proceedings%20were%20off%20the%20record.%20Fine.%20But%20since%20nothing%20had%20been%20agreed%20upon%20up%20to%20that%20point%2C%20I'm%20within%20my%20journalistic%20rights%20to%20report%20on%20the%20existence%20of%20the%20conference%20itself%20(which%20has%20also%20been%20reported%20on%20elsewhere)%20as%20well%20as%20the%20person%20who%20was%20onstage%20with%20Horowitz%20at%20the%20time%20he%20made%20the%20announcement.%20It%20was%20Neumann%2C%20as%20you've%20probably%20guessed.%20In%20a%20room%20full%20of%20Silicon%20Valley's%20elites%2C%20A16z%20was%20showing%20him%20off%20%E2%80%94%20and%20sending%20a%20message.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhy%20would%20they%20run%20out%20and%20give%20a%20bunch%20of%20money%20to%20Adam%20Neumann%20after%20everything%20they've%20seen%3F%20Like%2C%20what%20in%20the%20world%3F%20Was%20that%20all%20about%3F%26quot%3B%20said%20Benchmark's%20Gurley.%20(Gurley%20brought%20up%20A16z's%20investment%20in%20Flow%20independently%20in%20our%20conversation%20%E2%80%94%20we%20hadn't%20been%20discussing%20the%20conference%20and%20I%20don't%20know%20if%20he%20had%20attended%20it.)%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20were%20asked%20to%20analyze%20what%20they%20were%20doing%2C%20they%20wanted%20to%20send%20a%20signal%20to%20everyone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20signal%20was%20that%20they%20didn't%20care%20about%20reliability%20%E2%80%94%20they%20wanted%20founders%20who%20gave%20them%20upside%20risk.%20They%20were%20embracing%20variance.%20%26quot%3BIf%20they're%20that%20type%20of%20person%2C%20they're%20open%20for%20business%2C%20the%20door's%20wide%20open%2C%20and%20we're%20willing%20to%20talk%20to%20you%2C%20no%20matter%20what.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fnate-silver%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENate%20Silver%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3Eis%20the%20founder%20of%20FiveThirtyEight%20and%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20bestselling%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Signal%20and%20the%20Noise%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BOn%20the%20Edge.%26quot%3B%20He%20writes%20the%20Substack%20%26quot%3BSilver%20Bulletin.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EFrom%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.penguinrandomhouse.com%2Fbooks%2F529280%2Fon-the-edge-by-nate-silver%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EON%20THE%20EDGE%3A%20The%20Art%20of%20Risking%20Everything%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20by%20Nate%20Silver%2C%20published%20on%20August%2013%2C%202024%2C%20by%20Penguin%20Press%2C%20an%20imprint%20of%20Penguin%20Publishing%20Group%2C%20a%20division%20of%20Penguin%20Random%20House%20LLC.%20Copyright%20(c)%202024%20by%20Nate%20Silver.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstartup-success-secret-vcs-founders-nate-silver-on-the-edge-2024-8%5C%